Missing data¶

The field for active substance seems to better reflect the drugs compounds. However, there is substantial missing data for active substance. Here, the missing data is tackled by creating a "drug_name -> active_substance" dictionary and mapping the names to substances when missing.

In [169]:
len_data_deduped = len(drug_agg_df)
p_missing_drug_name = 100 * len(drug_agg_df[pd.isna(drug_agg_df['drug_name'])]) / len_data_deduped
p_missing_substance = 100 * len(drug_agg_df[pd.isna(drug_agg_df['active_substance'])]) / len_data_deduped

print(f'Missing drug name: {round(p_missing_drug_name, 3)} % \nMissing active substance: {round(p_missing_substance, 3)} %')

Missing drug name: 0.003 % 
Missing active substance: 31.141 %

# Create mapping dictionary between commercial names and substance names
drug_dict = dict(zip(drug_dict_df.drug_name, drug_dict_df.active_substance))

# Map commercial names to substance names
drug_agg_df['mapped_substance'] = drug_agg_df['drug_name'].map(drug_dict)

Analyse distribution of substances¶

Here, the goal is to explore the most reported drugs in the data. On top of that, the idea is also to obtain an insight of which drugs are administered together in the same adverse effect report. This is done by:

  1. Calculating the number of observations of different substances in the reports
  2. Visualizing the most observed drugs in the data
  3. For the most observed drugs, obtain the information of what drugs are more commonly administered together in the same adverse effect report
  4. For each of the drugs above, visualize how often other drugs are administered together (only for cases where multiple drugs are administered)

1. Get number of substance observations¶

In [98]:
drug_counts = drug_agg_df['mapped_substance'].value_counts().to_frame()
drug_counts['substance'] = drug_counts.index
In [99]:
drug_counts.rename(columns={'mapped_substance': 'drug_count'}, inplace=True)
In [100]:
drug_counts_subset = drug_counts[:20]

2. Visualize substance observations¶

In [103]:

3. Explore which drugs are more commonly administered together with most observed drugs¶

In [59]:
top_drugs = drug_agg_df['mapped_substance'].value_counts()[:30].index.tolist()
In [63]:
drug_values = {}
for drug in top_drugs:
    rep_df = drug_agg_df[drug_agg_df['mapped_substance']==drug]
    rep_ids = set(rep_df['rep_id'].values)
    other_drugs_df = drug_agg_df[(drug_agg_df['rep_id'].isin(rep_ids)) & (drug_agg_df['mapped_substance'] != drug)]
    drug_values[drug] = other_drugs_df['mapped_substance'].value_counts()

4. Visualize which are the substances more often associated with the most observed substances¶

In [164]:
# fig, axs = plt.subplots(5, 2)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(30,60))
fig.set_dpi(180)
# fig.set_figheight(15)
# fig.set_figwidth(25)
i = 1
for drug in top_drugs[:10]:
    drug_together = drug_values[drug].to_frame()
    drug_together['substance'] = drug_together.index
    drug_together.rename(columns={'mapped_substance': 'drug_count'}, inplace=True)
    drug_together['percent'] = 100 * drug_together['drug_count'] / sum(drug_together['drug_count'])
    drug_together_subset = drug_together[:10]
    
    ax = fig.add_subplot(5,2,i)
    ax.bar(drug_together_subset.substance, drug_together_subset.percent)
    ax.set_title(drug, fontdict={'fontsize': 18})
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=14, rotation = 60)
    ax.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=14)
    ax.set_ylabel('Joint substance use (%)', fontdict={'fontsize': 18})
    i = i +1
# plt.figure()
plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.5)
plt.show()

Extra: Time-dependant features¶

Another avenue that could be explored is how the incidence of certain drugs reported change yearly when compared to the total observations.

In [175]:
drug_agg_df['year'] = drug_agg_df['receipt_date'].astype(str).str[:4]
In [192]:
drug_year_df = drug_agg_df[['rep_id', 'year']].drop_duplicates()
aspirin_year_df = drug_agg_df[['rep_id', 'mapped_substance', 'year']].drop_duplicates()
yearly_observations = drug_year_df['year'].astype(int).value_counts()
yearly_observations_aspirin = aspirin_year_df[aspirin_year_df['mapped_substance']=='ASPIRIN']['year'].astype(int).value_counts()
In [193]:
yearly_observations = yearly_observations.to_frame().rename(columns={'year': 'observation_count'})

yearly_observations['Year'] = yearly_observations.index
yearly_observations_aspirin['Year'] = yearly_observations_aspirin.index
